The paper focuses on a deep generative model for image inpainting, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The proposed model is based on deep learning techniques, which are often associated with machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions a consistency loss, which is a common technique in graphics (GR) research. Finally, the proposed model is evaluated on three datasets, which suggests that multimedia (MM) could also be a relevant sub-category.
